<plot>The Pandolfi-Elmi family in central Italy's Umbria has been producing olive oil for centuries. Olga, Oriana, Luigi and Renato have been harvesting those olives for more than 50 years. A glimpse of the people, the landscape, and culture behind the harvest and the changing social fabric which threatens the future of this lyrical tradition.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?314128</url></doc>
